      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "638c91ab69edfcbb",
      "text": "With [[FairCoin2]], there is no reward for block creation. Therefore, the money supply is not further changed by creating blocks. A very small transaction fee goes to the respective block creators to compensate their efforts for running a CVN (energy and bandwidth costs).  Even if the network of CVNs may grows, the power consumption is negligibly low. CVNs can be run on a Raspberry3 which consumes only a couple of watts."
